  "prompt": "Can the same Jio SIM be used on two different mobile handsets?",
  "response": "No, the same Jio SIM card cannot be used simultaneously on two different mobile handsets. A SIM card is designed to be inserted into a single device at a time and is linked to that specific device's network connection. If you try to use the same SIM card on another phone, it will deactivate the connection on the first phone.\n\nHowever, you can physically remove the SIM card from one phone and insert it into another phone if you wish to switch devices. Just keep in mind that the SIM card will only be active in the device it is currently inserted into.\n\nIf you want to use two devices with the same Jio number, you might consider using Jio's **Multi-SIM feature**, which allows you to have multiple SIM cards linked to the same number (usually for use in different devices like a phone and a tablet). This feature is typically offered by Jio for postpaid plans, and you may need to contact Jio customer care to inquire about availability and activation.",
